canonical:
  title: 西都口號
  author: 李之氐
  language: lzh
  text: 大同江水瑠璃碧長樂宮花錦繡紅玉輦一遊非好事大平風月與民同
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 西都口號
  author: 李之氐
  language: lzh
  text: 大同江水瑠璃碧。長樂宮花錦繡紅。玉輦一遊非好事。大平風月與民同。
korean:
  title: 서도 구호
  author: 이지저
  language: kor
  text: |-
    대동강 물은 유리같이 푸르고
    장락궁 꽃은 비단같이 붉도다
    옥련(임금의 수레) 한 번 놂이 일 좋아함이 아닐세
    태평 풍월을 백성과 함께 하고저라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_020_0560&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 구호(口號) : '
    value: 시를 짓는데 즉석에서 입으로 부르는 것이다.
english:
  title: A Verse on the Western Capital
  author: Lee Ji-jeo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The waters of the Daedong River gleam like jade, their green so pure.
    The flowers of Jangnak Palace blaze like brocade in crimson hue.
    Yet the royal carriage's journey is no mere delight—
    I wish the peace and moonlight of this age to be shared with all the people.
  footnotes:
    - 'Daedong River: A river flowing through Pyongyang, the western capital of Korea.'
    - 'Jangnak Palace: A royal palace symbolizing the splendor of the capital.'
    - The poem contrasts the beauty of nature and imperial grandeur with a deeper concern for the common welfare, suggesting that true governance lies not in royal pleasure but in shared prosperity.
